  "prompt": "How is the placement at IIHMR Jaipur?",
  "response": "The Indian Institute of Health Management Research (IIHMR) in Jaipur is known for having a good placement record, particularly in the fields of healthcare management, pharmaceutical management, and rural development. Some key aspects of the placement scenario at IIHMR Jaipur include:\n\n1. **Industry Connections**: IIHMR Jaipur has strong ties with various segments of the healthcare industry, including hospitals, pharmaceutical companies, NGOs, international health organizations, and healthcare consulting firms. This network facilitates internships and placements for students.\n\n2. **Placement Support**: The institute has a dedicated placement cell that actively works to bring recruiters to campus and provide career guidance, resume building, interview preparation, and networking opportunities for students.\n\n3. **Recruiters**: Some notable recruiters at IIHMR Jaipur include Deloitte, Fortis Healthcare, Apollo Hospitals, Narayana Health, Johnson & Johnson, Baxter Healthcare, and various international and non-governmental organizations.\n\n4. **Salary Packages**: While the compensation can vary widely depending on the student\u2019s specialization, experience, and the recruiting organization, the overall placement packages tend to be competitive within the healthcare management domain.\n\n5. **Alumni Network**: The institute boasts a strong alumni network, which can be instrumental in helping students secure placements.\n\nFor the most accurate and updated information on placement statistics, including average packages and specific details about recruiters, you should consider looking at the most recent placement reports or directly contacting the IIHMR Jaipur\u2019s placement cell.",
